	<div id="discussion-comments">
	
		
			<ul class="comment b2" id="comment-7252020">
				
				<li class="comment-author" >
                    
                        <div class="badges">
                            
                                



                            
                        </div>
                        <div class="profile" >
                            
                                

<img class="author-profile-picture" src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2010/08/23/swedishrockstar/25714eba-9f37-4117-ab7e-7c292b3c3d7a/60x60.png" height="60" width="60" alt="" />
<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/discussion/user/swedishrockstar" title="User profile page">swedishrockstar</a>

                            
                            <p class="date">17 December 2009 11:15AM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Beef dripping, no parboiling, cook at the same temp as your meat for around 1hr 20. Baste and turn them once and they'll be great.
</p><p>No shaking, fluffing and certainly no sprinkling of anything to alter their texture.
</p><p>What's the obsession with 'fluffy' potatoes? They're spuds - they should be big, ugly pieces of stodgy carb to go alongside the other bits of your roast.
</p><p>If you want something light and fluffy, I'd suggest an Angel Delight afterwards.</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
