					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Masher trick - yes, exactly as Vicky says, St J gently pushed the almost roasted potatoes down to increase the surface area on the pan. It crisped 'em up a treat - a bit too much in fact, I'd say, (yes, such a thing <i>is</i> possible). I loved too, the fact that Jamie rated his three spud techniques thusly: the ones with oil and rosemary and garlic, he gave 10 out of 10, the goosefat with thyme and garlic went "off the richter scale" and the butter ones were the ones he said he'd be doing himself this year, so good were they. Good fella. That's the kind of rating I like to give my stuff. :)</p>
						
