<img class="author-profile-picture" src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/site_furniture/2010/09/01/no-user-image.gif" height="60" width="60" alt="" />
<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/discussion/user/halloweenwitch" title="User profile page">halloweenwitch</a>

                            
                            <p class="date">17 December 2009 1:04PM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>I love this article!
</p><p>I par-boil for about 10 mins (with the peelings), drain, chuck in a big lump of butter, add some rosmary, salt and pepper, put the lid on a shake (alot). Then chuck them in a tray that has been in a hot oven with a good drizzle of olive oil so that thay sizzle on contact and then chuck them in the oven until they look the right colour. Yum.
</p><p>Im going to try replacing olive oil with ground nut though and I love the taste testing different potatoes, always wanted to but could never be bothered! Will be going for a Maris piper this christmas : )</p>
						
					</div>
