                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Maris Pipers have been my preferred choice for roasties for a long time now.  I put them in cold salted water and bring them up to the boil, parboil for 5 minutes and put them in a baking tray with beef dripping which has been heated on the hob.  Baste the potatoes whilst still on the heat for a couple of minutes just to seal them and then in the oven for one hour at gas mark 6.  
</p><p>Purfik!</p>
						
					</div>
