                            <p class="date">17 December 2009 1:54PM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>My Greek-Cypriot sister in law's recipe is superb:
</p><p>Parboil potatos for 10 mins, drain, fluff a bit, sprinkle with lots and lots of maldon salt and squeeze juice of one lemon over them. 
</p><p>Roast on high temperature, I sometimes add a little bit of finely chopped rosemary. 
</p><p>dont be put off by the lemon, it  makes them perfect for a fatty roast meat...</p>
						
					</div>
