					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>@poefaced
<br />I love love love the idea of your dyed roast potatoes. I sort of dyed mine a bit with mud, as I hadn't really scrubbed the potato skins enough, but do think boiling the peel really works
</p><p>@ginegecat, mugginsmonrieth, halloweenwitch
<br />Left to my own devices? I love some garlic and herbs in with them (particularly rosemary). But in interest of fairness, we did them without. Which is where heston's seasoning/peelings really made the difference I think
</p><p>@pepperonlilove
<br />My dad never used to parboil ahead of roasting, and his spuds while delicious, were always quite firm inside. But we weren't complaining. 
</p><p>@cerinamroth 
<br />I think your flour trick is probably a bit like nigella's semolina - adds to the crunch. Depends how crunchy you like them whether you need it!</p>
						
