                        <div class="profile" >
                            
                                

<img class="author-profile-picture" src="http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/discussion/avatars/2010/08/22/CBKeyWhy/b0c2ea38-dd1f-4bf5-82cc-18ecea74d094/60x60.png" height="60" width="60" alt="" />
<a href="http://www.guardian.co.uk/discussion/user/CBKeyWhy" title="User profile page">CBKeyWhy</a>

                            
                            <p class="date">17 December 2009 2:10PM</p>
                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>This may well be the most important article ever published! Investigative journalism at its finest. I was interested to hear about the freezing treatment. I recently started part cooking chips in the morning and refrigerating them until almost ready to serve the sausages/fish/omlettes/ et c and it is definitely worth doing if you have the time. (Unemployment has some things to recommend it.)It crisps them up nicely and has the added bonus of making it easier to co-ordinate timing with poached eggs and the like.</p>
						
					</div>
				</li>
				
