                        </div>
                    
					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Maybe this should be filed under 'Bleeding obvious' but after shaking the spuds a little I take the roasting pan and hot oil/lard/fat out of the oven and pour the liquid over the spuds in the pot. Shake a bit more including turning the pot (lid on obviously) upside down. Then pour back into roasting pan. The puds are then coated all over. Easier than flipping spuds once they are in the pan and quicker so fat/oil/lard stays hot.</p>
						
					</div>
