					<div class="comment-body">
						
							<p>Par boil for 8 minutes, rinse under cold water for fluffiness.  Get the fat (vegetable oil or juices from your roast) extremely hot, add the potatoes and then a very liberal sprinkling of salt.  This will ensure your roasties are nice and crispy.  Roast until done (usually arond half an hour in our oven). Perfect.  This is my mother's recipie and has been road tested countless times.</p>
						
